{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3551772,"name":"Peter F","username":"onthegrid007","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/o/85f322/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-09T08:47:45.915Z","cooked":"<p>Hello, so I seem to be having a problem with this code. The goal is to snap to the reef which is at increments of (360/6 sides = 60) degrees and when you are within range, disable snapping so you can align the reef to the arm of our robot. Mathmatically this is what we’ve come up with:</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="cpp"><code class="lang-cpp">const Translation2D m_alignTarget{reef target coords...};
const meter_t m_distanceThresh{25_in};
const degree_t m_snapToAngleNear{360}; // Stop snapping
const degree_t m_snapToAngleFar{360/6}; // Snap when far away
constexpr degree_t kGyroOffset{90_deg}; // Offset of the gyro mounted on the robot to get a zero heading...

...
// snap heading to reef
const Translation2d robotLocation{m_drive.GetPose().Translation()};

const meter_t distanceToTarget{robotLocation.Distance(m_alignTarget)};

const Translation2d delta{m_alignTarget - robotLocation};

const degree_t snapIncrement{(distanceToTarget &lt;= m_distanceThresh) ? m_snapToAngleNear : m_snapToAngleFar};

const degree_t rawAngle{degree_t{radian_t{atan2(delta.Y().value(), delta.X().value())}} + kGyroOffset};

const degree_t heading{std::round(rawAngle.value() / snapIncrement.value()) * snapIncrement};

const double errorTheta{mapval&lt;double, double, double, double, double&gt;(SwerveUtils::WrapAngle(radian_t(m_drive.GetAngle() - heading).value()), 0, 2 * std::numbers::pi, -std::numbers::pi, std::numbers::pi)};

const radians_per_second_t pidValueTheta{-m_setHeadingPID.Calculate(errorTheta)};

</code></pre>
<p>mapval maps (the first value) that comes in between (the second and third values) and outputs a value between (the 4th and 5th values)</p>
<p>SwerveUtils::WrapAngle wraps any angle around 2 pi to a value less then 2 pi</p>
<p>And finally pidValueTheta is set to the omega value on the drive command when the limelight is in range…</p>
<p>For some reason this code when starting the odometry at -90_deg and the robot rotated at 90 degrees it rotates around so the front of the robot faces the reef and snaps to the angle correctly but on the wrong face. Everything else I have tried has made the robot do random increments not facing the correct way at any point. Any ideas on whats wrong with this math please help us. Thank you.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":1,"updated_at":"2025-03-09T08:47:45.915Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":47,"readers_count":46,"score":24.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":494837,"topic_slug":"snap-set-heading-allignment-code","display_username":"Peter F","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":47080,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":" | CSA | ML & AI Programmer"},"post_url":"/t/snap-set-heading-allignment-code/494837/1","custom_user_title":" | CSA | ML & AI Programmer","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false}],"stream":[3551772]},"timeline_lookup":[[1,217]],"suggested_topics":[{"fancy_title":"Bad optional access when generating paths using PathPlanner","id":497333,"title":"Bad optional access when generating paths using PathPlanner","slug":"bad-optional-access-when-generating-paths-using-pathplanner","posts_count":5,"reply_count":2,"highest_post_number":